Sorry, I think I was not precise in my comment. My idea was to do the filtering in the callable, not to create a new method. The problem with creating a new method like this is that it duplicates the code. When changing something, one always needs to remember to change both locations.
I was thinking more about something like this:
    Observable.fromCallable(() -> {
                StatisticsItem statisticsData = DBReader.getStatistics();
                // Do the filtering loop here instead of in the main thread
                return foundFeed;
            })

